The game's good. But for those who want to try this game I remind you that this game is very difficult and challenging. And it took a very very long time to complete the game if you are F2P. Buying a premium general can help you a lot or just buy the victory medal for that juicy medals. Tips for f2p Save up medals don't waste it, here's a list of generals that are cheap but awesome: List, Tito, Heinrici, Smigly and Cavallero.

Read mission desc, look for primary and secondary objective, sort it from early turn to late turn, choose general based on situation, and try mapping Allies and your move on map, ALWAYS use reinforcement whether you need it or not, reinforcement can make campaign easier. Mission require more than 2 try, first try to scout mission area with plane or moving troops, Youre lucky if you beat it on first try. If WallStuck GRIND on AGrp mode and UFrnt and don't forget upgrading General,Tech, and Force

I love the game, the functions and features make it so much more realistic. But their is something that has to be changed, PLEASE MAKE IT SO THAT YOU CAN STACK NAVAL UNITS IN ARMY GROUP MODE. (Edit) the naval system in army group is not very good, not only can you not stack naval units to create fleets and escort troop transports, aircraft carriers have to go into to same area as an enemy to fight taking away their range advantage and leaving them vulnerable since they have no escorts.

I've made it far into the game and still haven't hit a paywall. Strategy actually does play a large role, and the large variety of different troop type upgrades all feel pretty unique and historically accurate (for the most part). And for once the bigger a cannon a unit possesses, the further its range which is a nice surprise. I'm tired of all the other games that have a rifle squad having the same firing range as an 18 inch naval cannon. Very fun and varied gameplay.

Love the game but has some issues There are a lot of little and big things I love about this game however I did have some bad experiences in the conquest mode. I am not a fan of the army group mechanism. I would prefer to control the entirety of the country rather than a portion. Second, we need the option to sell or dismiss generals. Most importantly I dont like that my generals are limited to their historical faction in campaign mode.
Great game overall just please improve AI!

Great Game, good Army Group Mode, only a couple of things when skipping the AIs turn in Army Group Mode, it also automatically resolves the battle if they attack you, which means if I want to fight the battles manually I have to wait through all of the AIs turn incase I get attacked which I think will need adjusted where it gives you the option to manually or automatically defend, and I've found it's very difficult to earn metals in this game which makes it difficult to progress the Campaign.

Absolutely great graphics, and new animations. I like artillery and Naval units cost less now. I also like the new system of Resupply/recruit However the "Cash" system where you start with a amount of money to buy one or 2 units needs a bit of work. For starters the air strikes cost more than a Infantry unit. The "Gold coins" they are fine. Navigating through the app is also more painful at first. Maybe explain the new metals and silver metals and stars? In tutorials. Also maybe add a multiplay
